"The good news is that the dogs are fine", says Whitmore.
"They're in good shape".
"They have been returned to their rightful owners".
Whitmore did not provide details on the location of the dogs or the circumstances that led to their discovery.
"The investigation is still ongoing".
"We don't want to say anything more", Whitmore said.
"We're following some leads".
The owners, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, were unavailable for comment on Thursday.
They took their two dogs in on Wednesday afternoon at a county animal shelter in Downey.
Sheriff's deputies found the van and the two dogs in different locations in Compton.
