But the Corgis Bunny and Peter, which Rickard and Peek were planning to present at the competition this week on behalf of their Japanese owners, were missing until Wednesday night.
Peek and Rickard, who live in Redding, were in town this weekend for the AKC/Eukanuba National Championship in Long Beach, because Trace was supposed to be competing.
As Peek's Times reported Wednesday, the other dogs were scheduled to compete in other competitions in the days leading up to the AKC/Eukanuba show.
Southern California is a stop on the couple's nearly month-long tour of dog shows.
Monday night, Peek and Rickard checked into the motel.
They often stayed in motels and parked their van outside their bedroom window.
They took three other dogs - a boxer, a Parson Russell Terrier, and a Brittany - to their motel room.
The thick-skinned Akitas and Corgis stayed in the van because it was cooler there.
They left the window wide open so the dogs could breathe fresh air.
Peek and Rickard reported their car stolen Tuesday at 6:00 a.m.
Peek promised a reward to anyone who could give him a clue to the Corgis, and the animals were implanted with microchips to identify them.
