China maintains its greenhouse gas reduction targets
China's representative at COP16 said that China has made enormous efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and that it would maintain its commitment to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45 percent by 2020.
China is sticking to its pledge to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45 percent by 2020, said Su Wei, the country's representative at COP16.
In his first public speech at the 16th United Nations Climate Change Conference (COP16), Su Wei assured that his country had made enormous efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and to transform its industry.
